dc_description_s:
GPS surveying shall establish photo-control points to check the new aerial photography. The location of the photo-control shall be strategically placed throughout the County in order to maintain the desired positional accuracy.  The origin of the photo-control survey; the Network - GPS field surveys for the supplemental photo-control will originate from First-order NGS and/or CALTRANS control stations.

NGS control station monuments are used as a primary source of horizontal survey control.  These primary control monuments are used to locate other surveys.
dc_publisher_s: Santa Rosa (Calif.). County Of Sonoma Gis Central.
